60|$|CHRIST. Why, I {{will tell}} you. Before I set foot out of doors, one night, as <b>I</b> <b>lay</b> <b>in</b> my <b>bed,</b> <b>I</b> {{had a dream}} about this; for, methought I saw two men, as like these as ever the world they could look, stand at my bed's feet, {{plotting}} how they might prevent my salvation. I will tell you their very words. They said (it was when I was in my troubles), What shall we do with this woman? for she cries out, waking and sleeping, for forgiveness. If she be suffered to go on as she begins, we shall lose her, as we have lost her husband. This, you know, might have made me take heed, and have provided when provision might have been had.|$|R
